{{Chess Opening Theory/Position|= |Amazon Attack | |rd|nd|bd|qd|kd|bd|nd|rd|= |pd|pd|pd| |pd|pd|pd|pd|= | | | | | | | | |= | | | |pd| | | | |= | | | |pl| | | | |= | | | |ql| | | | |= |pl|pl|pl| |pl|pl|pl|pl|= |rl|nl|bl| |kl|bl|nl|rl|= || }} =Amazon Attack = ===2. Qd3=== A rarely played move. A similar idea is the sunshine (1. d4 d5 2. Nc3 Nf6 3. Qd3) Played by William Pollock against Max Weiss in 1889. White lost.
